#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/duplicating/spin.rst:122
msgid "Duplicate vertices."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/duplicating/spin.rst:124
msgid "The spin operation leaves duplicate vertices along the profile. You can select all vertices at the seam with Border select :kbd:`B` (shown in Fig. :ref:`fig-mesh-screw-duplicate`) and perform a *Remove Doubles* operation."
msgstr "The spin operation leaves duplicate vertices along the profile. You can select all vertices at the seam with Border select :kbd:`B` (shown in Fig. :ref:`fig-mesh-screw-duplicate`) and perform a *Remove Doubles* operation."

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/duplicating/spin.rst:128
msgid "Notice the selected vertex count before and after the *Remove Doubles* operation ``Vertex count after removing doubles``. If all goes well, the final vertex count (38 in this example) should match the number of the original profile noted in :menuselection:`Mesh data --> Vertex and face numbers`. If not, some vertices were missed and you will need to weld them manually. Or, worse, too many vertices will have been merged."
msgstr "Notice the selected vertex count before and after the *Remove Doubles* operation ``Vertex count after removing doubles``. If all goes well, the final vertex count (38 in this example) should match the number of the original profile noted in :menuselection:`Dữ Liệu Khung Lưới (Mesh data) --> Số Điểm Đỉnh và Bề Mặt (Vertex and face numbers)`. If not, some vertices were missed and you will need to weld them manually. Or, worse, too many vertices will have been merged."

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/duplicating/spin.rst:135
msgid "Merging Two Vertices into One"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/duplicating/spin.rst:137
msgid "To merge (weld) two vertices together, select both of them by :kbd:`Shift-RMB` clicking on them. Press :kbd:`S` to start scaling and hold down :kbd:`Ctrl` while scaling to scale the points down to 0 units in the X, Y and Z axis. :kbd:`LMB` to complete the scaling operation and click the *Remove Doubles* button in the Tool Shelf in *Edit Mode* (also available with :menuselection:`Specials --> Remove Doubles`)."
msgstr "To merge (weld) two vertices together, select both of them by :kbd:`Shift-RMB` clicking on them. Press :kbd:`S` to start scaling and hold down :kbd:`Ctrl` while scaling to scale the points down to 0 units in the X, Y and Z axis. :kbd:`LMB` to complete the scaling operation and click the *Remove Doubles* button in the Tool Shelf in *Edit Mode* (also available with :menuselection:`Đặc Biệt (Specials) --> Xóa Điểm Đỉnh Kép (Remove Doubles)`)."

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/duplicating/spin.rst:143
msgid "Alternatively, you can use :menuselection:`Specials --> Merge` from the same *Specials* menu (or :kbd:`Alt-M`). Then, in the new pop-up menu, choose whether the merged vertex will be at the center of the selected vertices or at the 3D cursor. The first choice is better in our case!"
msgstr "Alternatively, you can use :menuselection:`Đặc Biệt (Specials) --> Hội Nhập (Merge)` from the same *Specials* menu (or :kbd:`Alt-M`). Then, in the new pop-up menu, choose whether the merged vertex will be at the center of the selected vertices or at the 3D cursor. The first choice is better in our case!"

